===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=仌,冫,氷,𣲝,𨻱,𣲙,仒}}
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r-p(w)am||to freeze; snow}} (provisionally reconstructed). Compare {{cog|sit-tan-pro|*pam||snow}}, {{cog|sit-jap|jpɣom||to freeze}}, {{m|sit-jap|tɤjpɣom||ice}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques, and Lai, 2019}}). Cognate with {{och-l|凌|ice}} and possibly {{och-l|凝|id=1|to congeal}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}). STEDT also includes {{och-l|雱|heavy (snowfall)}} and {{och-l|霙|snowflake}} in its Chinese comparandum.

Alternatively, this may be related to {{cog|okm|ប្រឹង|t=to harden; to solidify}}<ref>Jenner, P. 2009. Dictionary of Pre-Angkorian Khmer and Dictionary of Angkorian Khmer. Pacific Linguists. [http://sealang.net/oldkhmer/]</ref>, from {{m|okm|រឹង|t=to dry up}}, although the meanings are difficult to reconcile ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

